cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about fine-grained object classification using visual attention models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new network architecture, which involves learning attentiveness and discrimination of attention canvases, and building a dynamic internal representation for classification. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper deals with multimedia applications, it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, since the proposed network involves an LSTM recurrent unit, it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
